    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCan't drag floating windows.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPhase 1: Floating windows with a title or border can be repositioned with the mouse by dragging the title. Dragging the border resizes the window.\n\nPhase 2: Floating window can set a flag that makes its body draggable (this would prevent visual-selection with the mouse in that window). Or maybe a flag isn't needed; instead, a mapping can send `<LeftDrag>` while the window is focused, or use `nvim_input_mouse()`?\n\n",
